> Try:
> 
> 	compctl -D -f -x 'W[0,*=*] N[-1,:]' -/
> 
> See also Misc/compctl-examples in the zsh source.

Thanks a lot. The following seems to do what I want, namely enable file
completion after : and = anywhere on the command line.

compctl -D -f -x 'N[-1,:=]' -f

